<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 28 at 8:28PM CDT until July 28 at 8:45PM CDT by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 945 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN RHEA...CENTRAL BRADLEY...MEIGS...CENTRAL MCMINN AND
NORTHEASTERN HAMILTON COUNTIES...
At 928 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 6 miles northeast of Decatur to Lakesite, moving east
at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Athens, Sweetwater, Decatur, Soddy-Daisy, Lakesite,
Charleston, South Cleveland, East Cleveland and Harrison.
This includes Interstate 75 in Tennessee between mile markers 15 and
60.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.
Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
